The Professional Footballers’ Association (PFA) has announced the Premier League Team of the Year. There are five Liverpool players included. And they include goalkeeper Alisson Becker, right-back Trent Alexander-Arnold, defender Virgil van Dijk, midfielder Thiago Alcantara and forward Mohamed Salah. Manchester City have two of their stars in the XI – Joao Cancelo, Bernardo Silva and Kevin De Bruyne. Manchester United’s Cristiano Ronaldo and former Chelsea defender, Antonio Rudiger, also make the cut. PFA Premier League Team of the Year: Alisson – Liverpool
Trent Alexander-Arnold – Liverpool
Virgil van Dijk – Liverpool
Antonio Rudiger – Chelsea
Joao Cancelo – Manchester City
Kevin De Bruyne – Manchester City
Thiago Alcantara – Liverpool
Bernardo Silva – Manchester City
Sadio Mane – Liverpool
Cristiano Ronaldo – Manchester United
Mohamed Salah – Liverpool